  "texts": [
    "RECmin, in contrast, cannot detect events greater than 300 s, and RECmax skews towards longer events, likely missing the large subset of shorter, potentially real events detected by multi-STA/LTA.",
    "The total energy of events detected by both multi-STA/LTA and RECmin plots as a near-symmetric peak, but RECmax does not detect the lower-energy events.",
    "All three algorithms show detections for approximately 50 events at very large energies, greater than 10 log (a.u.).",
    "The distributions of the high-and low-confidence multi-STA/LTA events are similar for higher durations (> 1 log, seconds), energies (> 5 log, a.u.",
    "), and amplitudes (> 3 log, a.u.)."
